
Syntax: f_ind "text"   
        l_ocate "text"
        f_ind ["text"] A=login
        l_ocate ["text"] A=login

Description: This will show all lines of responses in the current
   item which contain the specified string of text.  In the latter 
   forms, all responses by the login specified will be found, and 
   the first line of each displayed, unless a text string is also 
   specified.  If both an author and text are given as arguments, 
   all lines of responses by the author specified which contain the 
   specified text will be shown.

See also: range
